{
  "texts": [
    "Smaller yet proficient encoder-only models offer a pragmatic compromise, emphasizing task-specific efficiency without compromising on overall performance.",
    "Consequently, the selection of model architecture should be tailored to the specific requirements and trade-offs inherent in each application scenario.The limitations of this study include the exclusive focus on LLaMA2 for decoder-only architectures and a confined scope to sentiment analysis and intent classification tasks.",
    "The reliance on publicly available datasets may introduce variability compared to using private ones, as these dataset were likely used to pre-train the model.",
    "Computational constraints, limited to a single NVIDIA V100 GPU, influenced the choice of models.",
    "While various prompts were explored, it was not the primary focus of this study, and the optimal one wasn't specifically sought."
  ]
}